reviewText: A terrible explanation about Lizzie Borden! The acting in this terrible It's a bunch of twentysomethings running around like dingdong's.  And the quality of the filmmaking as poor as well.
Great movie. I love scary movies. This one is a great one.
This is the only movie I have ever thrown in the garbage.

A group of college friends finds a "true-good-to-be-true" deal on a house they rent, with an owner who has just a bit of "sinister" in her. What could go wrong? How about: it's haunted by a spirit who has a direct relationship to one of the girls in the group!

A great evening's entertainment for teen and adult audiences.
